    <% main_text: 'Challenge #1: Crowdsourcing 9-1-1: Scrubbing Social Media sources during disasters to generate situational awareness and residential needs.', %>
    <% detail_paragraphs: ['We know that social media sources provide vital information for rescuers &ndash; both formal first responders and community responders &ndash; to help residents needing assistance throughout a disaster area. 9-1-1 architecture can be overwhelmed and damaged in disaster events and social media has been shown to augment this overwhelm by providing alternative means of communication.', 'Additionally apps like Zello &ndash; a point to point radio application &ndash; and other tools (google, open street map, etc) can make response groups like the Cajun Navy, community response organizations, open mapping projects and Virtual Operations Support Teams (VOSTs).', 'How might social media be used by formal responders to better help residents in need when 9-1-1 architecture becomes overwhelmed? How might these two types of organizations partner better to protect residents during an emergency?'], %>
